CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 7, 1941, pg. 18, reads: "Central Baptist Fetes Its Youthful Pastor And Wife" - Words of praise and commendation flowed like water and were as plentiful as the delicious chicken a la king at the banquet Monday night in Central Baptist Church for the Rev. and Mrs. Cornell E. Talley..Staff photos by Harris"
TitMainTitle: Group from left: two unknown men and women, Mrs. W. D. Battles behind potted fern, John Cavanaugh, Martha Talley, Rev. Cornell E. Talley, Mr. and Mrs. Tinker, Mrs. Charles P. Pernell, and Andrew Parks wearing dark suit, seated at long banquet table, in Central Baptist Church
